course: main course
---

Wash and dry all produce. Halve @grape tomatoes{4%ounce}. Trim and thinly slice
@scallions{2}, separating whites from greens. Mince @cilantro{1/4%ounce}. Zest
and quarter @lime{1}. Mince @chili pepper{1}.

Melt @butter{1%tbsp} in a #small pot{} over medium-high heat. Add half the
scallion whites and 1/4 tsp @turmeric{1%tsp}(divided); cook until fragrant,
~{1%minute}. Stir in @jasmine rice{1/2%cup}, @mushroom stock concentrate{1},
3/4 cup water, and a big pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a boil, then cover and
reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}. Keep
covered off heat until ready to serve.

Meanwhile, in a #medium bowl{}, combine tomatoes, cilantro, remaining
scallion whites, and juice from half the lime. Season with @salt{} and
@pepper{}. If you like spicy food, stir in chili to taste.

In a #small bowl{}, combine @sour cream{2%tbsp}, a large squeeze of lime juice,
and as much lime zest as you like. Stir in water 1 tsp at a time until
mixture reaches a drizzling consistency. Season with salt and pepper.

In a second small bowl, combine @cumin{1%tsp} and 1/4 tsp turmeric. Pat
@rockfish{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}. Season all over with salt,
pepper, and spice mixture. Heat a large drizzle of @vegetable oil{2%tsp} in a
#large nonstick pan{} over medium-high heat. Add rockfish and cook until opaque
and cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes} per side.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in scallion greens and @butter{1%tbsp} and
season with salt and pepper. Divide between plates. Top rice with rockfish;
garnish with salsa fresca and crema. Serve with any remaining lime wedges on
the side.

> Salsa fresca is our favorite way to feel warm weather vibes all year round. It's
> juicy and tangy with a touch of heat, making it the perfect complement to
> crispy, turmeric-and-cumin-spiced rockfish. The feisty fillets are served on
> top of steamy yellow rice and blanketed in lime crema and said salsa. No matter
> the temperature, one bite of this delicious dish will make everything feel a
> whole lot sunnier.